11
00:01:19.913 --> 00:01:21.039
[grunts]

12
00:01:24.960 --> 00:01:26.044
[groans]

13
00:01:27.171 --> 00:01:30.174
[panting]

14
00:01:43.854 --> 00:01:46.773
[melancholic music playing]

15
00:01:49.568 --> 00:01:51.820
[straining]

16
00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:00.662
[grunts]

17
00:02:02.289 --> 00:02:03.874
[breathing heavily]

18
00:02:09.045 --> 00:02:11.297
[metallic tapping in distance]

19
00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:12.381
[sniffs]

20
00:02:12.382 --> 00:02:13.634
[music stops]

21
00:02:18.889 --> 00:02:21.141
[tapping continues]

22
00:02:34.530 --> 00:02:36.448
[knocking]

23
00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:42.663
[knocking continues]

24
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:48.293
[hatch opens]

25
00:02:49.127 --> 00:02:50.712
[hatch closes. locks]

26
00:03:07.062 --> 00:03:08.146
[coughs]

27
00:03:09.398 --> 00:03:11.441
[interrogator. in Russian]
Are you ready to write your confession?

28
00:03:14.528 --> 00:03:16.405
Still nothing?

29
00:03:20.909 --> 00:03:23.662
How many times must we go through this?

30
00:03:27.708 --> 00:03:28.709
[scoffs]

31
00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:31.377
Fine.

32
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:33.130
We will try again another day.

33
00:03:33.547 --> 00:03:35.090
[Irina] This is an outrage.

34
00:03:37.467 --> 00:03:40.971
A person of my position.
treated like this.

35
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:45.309
You are not being punished.
Comrade Morozova.

36
00:03:46.018 --> 00:03:47.686
You are being…

37
00:03:48.604 --> 00:03:49.897
rehabilitated.

38
00:03:51.064 --> 00:03:53.065
And how long will that take?

39
00:03:53.066 --> 00:03:55.444
Until you are rehabilitated.

40
00:03:57.738 --> 00:03:59.406
You think I am scared of you?

41
00:04:00.574 --> 00:04:05.078
I was running security at Star City…

42
00:04:06.288 --> 00:04:07.372
when you

43
00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.209
were a pimply teenager

44
00:04:10.626 --> 00:04:13.420
fucking the family goat.

45
00:04:15.005 --> 00:04:16.005
[grunts]

46
00:04:16.798 --> 00:04:18.175
[screams]

47
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:24.640
We will try again another day.

48
00:04:31.563 --> 00:04:32.731
[strains]

49
00:04:39.696 --> 00:04:42.032
[Irina]
<i>I have faithfully served my country…</i>

50
00:04:42.407 --> 00:04:45.076
and this is my reward?!

51
00:04:45.077 --> 00:04:46.203
[groans. shouts]

52
00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:49.706
[strains]

53
00:04:52.668 --> 00:04:55.795
Open up and let me out of here!

54
00:04:55.796 --> 00:04:57.171
[yelps]

55
00:04:57.172 --> 00:05:00.175
[grunts. pants]

56
00:05:06.849 --> 00:05:09.017
[Irina shouting in Russian]

57
00:05:11.270 --> 00:05:12.271
[screams]

58
00:05:14.815 --> 00:05:15.816
[grunts]

59
00:05:16.400 --> 00:05:17.568
[groans]

60
00:05:19.027 --> 00:05:20.362
[screams]

61
00:05:21.071 --> 00:05:22.281
[sighs]

62
00:05:23.574 --> 00:05:26.910
[hatch opening. closing]

63
00:05:30.414 --> 00:05:31.497
[sighs]

64
00:05:31.498 --> 00:05:33.792
- [door opens]
- [guard 1 speaking Russian]

65
00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:37.129
[guard 1 speaking Russian]

66
00:05:37.629 --> 00:05:39.840
[guard 2 speaking Russian]

67
00:05:42.467 --> 00:05:44.178
[guards speaking Russian]

68
00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:49.183
[metallic tapping]

69
00:06:04.615 --> 00:06:06.366
[tapping]

70
00:06:12.873 --> 00:06:14.750
[interrogator]
<i>I'm glad you've come to your senses.</i>

71
00:06:16.335 --> 00:06:19.545
Your confession will be
well-received in Moscow.

72
00:06:19.546 --> 00:06:20.547
[pencil scribbling]

73
00:06:21.256 --> 00:06:22.674
19 months.

74
00:06:23.509 --> 00:06:26.220
Most do not last nearly that long.

75
00:06:29.264 --> 00:06:30.933
- [scribbling stops]
- [pencil clatters]

76
00:06:37.356 --> 00:06:38.440
What is this?

77
00:06:39.441 --> 00:06:42.152
This is what you will do for me.

78
00:06:45.405 --> 00:06:46.906
[laughs. stammers]

79
00:06:46.907 --> 00:06:48.325
What I will do for you?

80
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:52.162
Semyon Ivanovich Petrikov.

81
00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:56.375
Resident of 26 Valovaya Street.

82
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:58.836
Son of Lyubov and Ivan.

83
00:06:59.086 --> 00:07:00.504
Brother of Roksana.

84
00:07:01.880 --> 00:07:03.090
You have enemies…

85
00:07:03.715 --> 00:07:07.219
who wish to see you pay
for your crimes in this place.

86
00:07:08.095 --> 00:07:09.304
And I still have friends…

87
00:07:10.013 --> 00:07:12.766
who wish to see me free.

88
00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:15.394
After I am released…

89
00:07:15.769 --> 00:07:17.938
you will never hear from me again.

90
00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:21.483
If you fail to comply and I remain here…

91
00:07:21.984 --> 00:07:24.611
you will find yourself alone in the world.

92
00:07:24.945 --> 00:07:26.822
You will bury your entire family…

93
00:07:27.281 --> 00:07:29.157
and you will be waiting for
a knife in the dark

94
00:07:29.575 --> 00:07:31.451
for the rest of your days.

95
00:07:36.582 --> 00:07:37.583
How…

96
00:07:39.877 --> 00:07:40.878
How do you know about my family?

97
00:07:41.837 --> 00:07:43.589
Who told you about my family?

98
00:07:53.682 --> 00:07:55.976
I believe I am rehabilitated

99
00:07:57.352 --> 00:07:59.188
Comrade Petrikov.

100
00:08:12.910 --> 00:08:14.536
[breathing shakily]

101
00:08:34.264 --> 00:08:36.642
[exhales deeply]

102
00:08:48.153 --> 00:08:49.988
[theme music playing]

103
00:09:59.016 --> 00:10:02.185
[in English] This shocking data breach.
which was anonymously given

104
00:10:02.186 --> 00:10:07.106
to reporters working for the NNC network
on Mars. has exposed classified documents

105
00:10:07.107 --> 00:10:10.276
from within the highest levels
of government and commerce.

106
00:10:10.277 --> 00:10:14.864
The leaked files and d-mails primarily
center on plans by the nations of the M-6

107
00:10:14.865 --> 00:10:18.910
and prominent aerospace corporations.
Kuragin and Helios.

108
00:10:18.911 --> 00:10:22.747
to automate all mining
and most other Mars industries.

109
00:10:22.748 --> 00:10:26.042
Those responsible for the breach
have not yet been identified.

110
00:10:26.043 --> 00:10:30.046
Governor Polivanov has been intensely
criticized by residents of Mars

111
00:10:30.047 --> 00:10:31.964
for the secret automation plan.

112
00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:34.759
undermining his position
on the Red Planet.

113
00:10:34.760 --> 00:10:36.177
[reporter] Governor. will you resign?

114
00:10:36.178 --> 00:10:37.513
[Lenya speaks Russian]

115
00:10:37.846 --> 00:10:41.266
At this week's Party Congress.
President Korzhenko expressed

116
00:10:41.475 --> 00:10:44.478
his displeasure regarding
the illegal Martian data breach

117
00:10:44.937 --> 00:10:47.813
the latest in a series of missteps
by the Governor of Mars.

118
00:10:47.814 --> 00:10:49.900
Leonid Aleksandrovich Polivanov.

119
00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:52.443
Once the heir-apparent to Korzhenko…

120
00:10:52.444 --> 00:10:57.073
many in the Party are now calling into
question his fitness for higher office.

121
00:10:57.074 --> 00:11:00.952
[in English] In response to the leaked
documents. small protests have broken out

122
00:11:00.953 --> 00:11:04.455
across Happy Valley
with residents voicing their concerns.

123
00:11:04.456 --> 00:11:08.960
What do you say to those who don't
understand why you all are so upset?

124
00:11:08.961 --> 00:11:10.294
Where are you from?

125
00:11:10.295 --> 00:11:11.838
[reporter] Uh. Florida.

126
00:11:11.839 --> 00:11:14.382
So imagine they decided not only
to shut down Disney World

127
00:11:14.383 --> 00:11:16.008
and fire everybody who works there.

128
00:11:16.009 --> 00:11:18.553
but kick out everyone
who lives in Orlando.

129
00:11:18.554 --> 00:11:22.098
We need them to listen to us
and stop the automation.

130
00:11:22.099 --> 00:11:23.182
Mars is ours.

131
00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:26.227
[residents chanting]
Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

132
00:11:26.228 --> 00:11:29.564
Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

133
00:11:29.565 --> 00:11:34.861
Mars is ours!

134
00:11:34.862 --> 00:11:36.446
[chanting continues]

135
00:11:41.994 --> 00:11:43.495
[chanting continues]

136
00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:54.505
- Alex. Alex. Hey. Thank God.
- Hi. Yeah.

137
00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:55.923
Can you believe this?

138
00:11:55.924 --> 00:11:57.426
This is amazing.

139
00:11:58.010 --> 00:11:59.552
I mean. we did this.

140
00:11:59.553 --> 00:12:01.805
- [chuckles]
- Yeah. Yeah.

141
00:12:02.306 --> 00:12:03.932
Yeah. we really… [mumbles]

142
00:12:04.433 --> 00:12:06.226
[crowd chanting. clamoring]

143
00:12:07.102 --> 00:12:09.146
You don't… You don't think
that they're looking for us. do you?

144
00:12:10.147 --> 00:12:11.148
I feel like we're fine.

145
00:12:11.648 --> 00:12:13.774
If they knew.
they would've arrested us already. right?

146
00:12:13.775 --> 00:12:16.028
Right. Yeah. [chuckles] Yeah.

147
00:12:17.070 --> 00:12:18.071
[both chuckle]

148
00:12:21.950 --> 00:12:23.202
[clamoring continues]

149
00:12:24.745 --> 00:12:25.995
Peacekeepers. my ass.

150
00:12:25.996 --> 00:12:27.246
Go back to Earth. peckers!

151
00:12:27.247 --> 00:12:29.874
Okay. All right. You made your point.
Move along. Thank you.

152
00:12:29.875 --> 00:12:32.251
Well. look who decided to show up. huh?

153
00:12:32.252 --> 00:12:33.503
Couldn't stay away. could you?

154
00:12:33.504 --> 00:12:35.547
Yeah. They pulled me off sick leave early.

155
00:12:36.256 --> 00:12:38.550
- All hands on deck. I guess.
- Yeah. well. Shit.

156
00:12:39.218 --> 00:12:40.302
I'm happy you're back.

157
00:12:41.053 --> 00:12:42.887
- Have you read it?
- Yeah. I read it.

158
00:12:42.888 --> 00:12:44.597
Honestly. I don't know
what all the fuss is about.

159
00:12:44.598 --> 00:12:47.016
You'd think it was a bunch
of naked pictures of Gisele Bündchen.

160
00:12:47.017 --> 00:12:48.267
Fred… [stammers]

161
00:12:48.268 --> 00:12:51.437
It says peacekeepers were working security
for those Kuragin night shipments.

162
00:12:51.438 --> 00:12:54.315
Yeah. so? You know. cops moonlight
as security back on Earth all the time.

163
00:12:54.316 --> 00:12:57.068
- So what?
- Yoon Tae-min worked those shipments.

164
00:12:57.069 --> 00:13:00.112
And when he showed up dead.
not one MPK thought to say anything.

165
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:01.406
You're back on this. huh?

166
00:13:04.409 --> 00:13:07.412
Yeah. If Lee's really innocent.
we have to set this right.

167
00:13:08.497 --> 00:13:10.414
Look. the peacekeepers
working security that night

168
00:13:10.415 --> 00:13:11.749
might have seen Yoon before he died.

169
00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:14.794
- So?
- So. they could've noticed something.

170
00:13:14.795 --> 00:13:18.422
Look. dispatch is supposed to have
records of all security work on the base.

171
00:13:18.423 --> 00:13:23.094
but I could not find anything about
MPKs or those Kuragin night shipments.

172
00:13:23.095 --> 00:13:25.179
Fred. there is not a single record of it.

173
00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:26.514
So what are you saying?

174
00:13:26.515 --> 00:13:28.724
That someone is trying
to cover something up.

175
00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:32.144
Come on. Man. th-these are the people
you should be focused on right here.

176
00:13:32.145 --> 00:13:33.896
- They have the right to be angry.
- I know.

177
00:13:33.897 --> 00:13:35.523
- They're angry with us.
- Yeah.

178
00:13:35.524 --> 00:13:37.234
Maybe they should be.

179
00:13:39.319 --> 00:13:41.112
Okay. Okay. yeah.

180
00:13:41.113 --> 00:13:43.447
I can see you are clearly
not gonna drop this.

181
00:13:43.448 --> 00:13:45.409
So let me ask around for you. all right?

182
00:13:45.951 --> 00:13:49.580
I've got a friend who works in records. If
you. uh. go charging in there like usual.

183
00:13:50.080 --> 00:13:52.666
you're on the first transport
out of here. so don't.

184
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:54.876
Thank you. I really appreciate that.

185
00:13:54.877 --> 00:13:56.253
Well. what can I say. C?

186
00:13:56.753 --> 00:13:59.338
- You're growing on me.
- Yeah. [chuckles] Like a fungus.

187
00:13:59.339 --> 00:14:00.924
Yeah. Exactly like a fungus.

188
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:04.010
- [laughs] Oh. shit.
- Oh. shit.

189
00:14:04.011 --> 00:14:05.762
That's actually a really good one.
[laughs]

190
00:14:09.308 --> 00:14:10.350
See you up there. Miles.

191
00:14:10.934 --> 00:14:11.935
You bet.

192
00:14:25.324 --> 00:14:26.575
What do you want?

193
00:14:28.243 --> 00:14:29.244
The leak.

194
00:14:30.204 --> 00:14:31.830
- What do you know about it?
- Nothing.

195
00:14:32.414 --> 00:14:33.540
[sighs]

196
00:14:34.917 --> 00:14:38.294
Any of those Free Mars idiots
bragging and taking credit for it?

197
00:14:38.295 --> 00:14:41.005
No. Other than being pissed off.
and I don't blame them.

198
00:14:41.006 --> 00:14:42.548
[scoffs] Boo-hoo.

199
00:14:42.549 --> 00:14:45.343
Oh. come on. Palmer.
You can't be okay with this.

200
00:14:45.344 --> 00:14:48.638
Them shipping us all home?
You've been up here too.

201
00:14:48.639 --> 00:14:51.015
Living. working. same as me.
Same as all of us.

202
00:14:51.016 --> 00:14:53.644
- This is your home.
- [laughs] Home?

203
00:14:54.311 --> 00:14:55.729
You've gotta be kidding me.

204
00:14:58.148 --> 00:15:01.443
Do you know why
I got into law enforcement. Dale?

205
00:15:02.528 --> 00:15:04.654
We don't belong here.

206
00:15:04.655 --> 00:15:06.698
Not long-term anyway.

207
00:15:09.284 --> 00:15:11.245
Ever since '03. I saw it.

208
00:15:12.746 --> 00:15:13.830
Something about the…

209
00:15:14.831 --> 00:15:16.082
the gravity.

210
00:15:16.083 --> 00:15:17.709
It does something to your brain.

211
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:19.919
This ain't home.

212
00:15:19.920 --> 00:15:22.965
This is just temporary at best.

213
00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:26.926
I brought my family up here.

214
00:15:26.927 --> 00:15:28.011
So many of us did.

215
00:15:29.179 --> 00:15:32.558
Yeah. Well. I'm very familiar
with your family. Dale.

216
00:15:34.560 --> 00:15:36.228
Your youngest in particular.

217
00:15:40.065 --> 00:15:41.316
What does that mean?

218
00:15:42.276 --> 00:15:44.987
The files were illegally given to NNC.

219
00:15:45.904 --> 00:15:47.573
Isn't that where your daughter works?

220
00:15:49.950 --> 00:15:51.368
It couldn't have been Lily. I mean…

221
00:15:51.869 --> 00:15:53.452
she was at home with me and Amanda.

222
00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:56.540
[scoffs] Just stop.
You-You're embarrassing yourself now.

223
00:15:57.082 --> 00:15:59.877
I know Lily leaked the files. Dale.

224
00:16:01.420 --> 00:16:02.671
What I need to know

225
00:16:04.214 --> 00:16:05.674
is who gave them to her.

226
00:16:08.302 --> 00:16:10.052
I don't know what you're talking about.

227
00:16:10.053 --> 00:16:11.054
Hmm.

228
00:16:11.889 --> 00:16:14.308
Well. you better find out.

229
00:16:15.434 --> 00:16:18.019
Because this is
national security shit here.

230
00:16:18.020 --> 00:16:20.313
There were classified documents in there.

231
00:16:20.314 --> 00:16:24.193
This is 20 years in prison
at the very least.

232
00:16:26.737 --> 00:16:27.946
Or…

233
00:16:28.614 --> 00:16:31.200
she could just share a cell
with your good buddy Sam Massey.

234
00:16:34.286 --> 00:16:35.621
[grunts]

235
00:16:37.623 --> 00:16:39.207
[chuckles]

236
00:16:39.208 --> 00:16:41.210
Yeah. You must wanna go with her. huh?

237
00:16:45.506 --> 00:16:46.798
[sighs]

238
00:16:50.093 --> 00:16:51.136
[sighs]

239
00:16:53.347 --> 00:16:54.765
You've got until tomorrow.

240
00:16:58.435 --> 00:16:59.519
[door closes]

241
00:16:59.520 --> 00:17:00.562
Shit.

242
00:17:03.065 --> 00:17:04.066
[sighs]

243
00:17:07.903 --> 00:17:08.945
[assistant] Dev?

244
00:17:09.780 --> 00:17:11.322
Ms. Rosales wants to…

245
00:17:11.323 --> 00:17:12.990
Uh. she's… she's coming in.

246
00:17:12.991 --> 00:17:14.992
Yeah. I'm coming in.

247
00:17:15.743 --> 00:17:17.912
Because I'm the CEO of this company.

248
00:17:17.913 --> 00:17:19.664
I am not a middle manager.

249
00:17:19.665 --> 00:17:22.625
You said we were partners. Now
you wanna turn around and do this shit?

250
00:17:22.626 --> 00:17:24.919
[Dev] I didn't tell you because I knew
that you wouldn't agree to it.

251
00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:26.504
That's right. Because it's a bad idea.

252
00:17:26.505 --> 00:17:28.256
We didn't have a choice.

253
00:17:28.257 --> 00:17:31.133
You thought automation
wasn't coming with or without us?

254
00:17:31.134 --> 00:17:32.426
This way we can control it

255
00:17:32.427 --> 00:17:34.804
- and make it work for us.
- How inspiring.

256
00:17:34.805 --> 00:17:36.806
This coming from the woman
that pitched me robotics ten years ago?

257
00:17:36.807 --> 00:17:39.851
You made an unauthorized deal
with our main competitor.

258
00:17:39.852 --> 00:17:42.353
Your buddies on the board
are gonna lose it.

259
00:17:42.354 --> 00:17:44.897
Meru can be built twice as quickly
with automated equipment.

260
00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:46.941
Oh. fuck your Legoland.

261
00:17:46.942 --> 00:17:48.944
Do you understand
the position you've put me in?

262
00:17:49.444 --> 00:17:52.071
If it becomes public
that I was in the dark about this.

263
00:17:52.072 --> 00:17:53.656
our stock would tank even more.

264
00:17:53.657 --> 00:17:55.825
And our competitors
will smell blood in the water.

265
00:17:55.826 --> 00:17:56.909
[door opens]

266
00:17:56.910 --> 00:18:00.079
Uh. the Kuragin delegation is arriving.

267
00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:02.165
Thank you. Zuzana. A minute. please?

268
00:18:11.967 --> 00:18:17.139
I cannot be an effective leader
of this company. our company.

269
00:18:18.724 --> 00:18:20.934
with you undercutting me at every turn.

270
00:18:22.769 --> 00:18:25.606
Things have to change if we're
gonna make it through this crisis.

271
00:18:27.941 --> 00:18:29.693
And right now that's a big fucking "if."

272
00:18:32.821 --> 00:18:33.906
[door opens]

273
00:18:41.872 --> 00:18:42.873
[in Russian] Comrade Bolkonski.

274
00:18:43.373 --> 00:18:45.958
It is an honor to welcome
the Kuragin Corporation to Mars.

275
00:18:45.959 --> 00:18:50.130
[speaks Russian] I am happy
to visit your cute little colony.

276
00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:52.673
[speaks Russian]

277
00:18:52.674 --> 00:18:54.134
[both speaking Russian]

278
00:19:06.313 --> 00:19:09.358
Welcome to Happy Valley. Comrade Morozova.

279
00:19:10.108 --> 00:19:11.652
It has been awhile.

280
00:19:11.944 --> 00:19:13.152
Yes.

281
00:19:13.153 --> 00:19:14.947
It seems we have much to discuss.

282
00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:18.158
- [speaks Russian]
- [in English] Hi.

283
00:19:25.958 --> 00:19:27.543
[spouse. in Russian]
I don't like that she's here…

284
00:19:28.752 --> 00:19:29.962
not with me leaving.

285
00:19:30.295 --> 00:19:31.588
I can handle her.

286
00:19:31.797 --> 00:19:34.257
She was Second Directorate in the KGB.

287
00:19:34.258 --> 00:19:36.051
I am aware
of her previous employment. darling.

288
00:19:36.552 --> 00:19:38.636
She was at Star City
the entire time I was there.

289
00:19:38.637 --> 00:19:41.348
But she handles security for Kuragin now.

290
00:19:41.807 --> 00:19:43.641
[spouse] You never leave the KGB. Lenya.

291
00:19:43.642 --> 00:19:45.060
You know this.

292
00:19:49.731 --> 00:19:52.276
[in English] Well.
thank you all for coming. [sighs]

293
00:19:52.985 --> 00:19:55.945
Now. while I had hoped that
this meeting would be about us

294
00:19:55.946 --> 00:19:58.448
trying to get our operations
back on schedule.

295
00:19:59.074 --> 00:20:01.534
the events have overtaken the agenda.

296
00:20:01.535 --> 00:20:04.704
Don't you think it's wise
to pause any further automation work

297
00:20:04.705 --> 00:20:07.415
until things calm down a bit more?

298
00:20:07.416 --> 00:20:09.625
Now. we have five souls
on a mission to Titan

299
00:20:09.626 --> 00:20:11.586
- that requires our full attention...
- Mmm. no. no.

300
00:20:11.587 --> 00:20:15.631
This is exactly
what the agitators are calling for.

301
00:20:15.632 --> 00:20:18.426
We give in to them now.
they will only ask for more.

302
00:20:18.427 --> 00:20:22.555
The M-6 still believes that it is
in the best interests of Mars

303
00:20:22.556 --> 00:20:24.348
for us to continue on the same schedule.

304
00:20:24.349 --> 00:20:26.309
A schedule that is now public.

305
00:20:26.310 --> 00:20:29.020
Thanks to a data breach
from within your company.

306
00:20:29.021 --> 00:20:32.398
Which was intended to expose
unethical work practices at your company.

307
00:20:32.399 --> 00:20:35.026
[Dev] All right. all right.
We all want the same thing here. okay.

308
00:20:35.027 --> 00:20:37.196
We can't have chaos here
on this base. not again.

309
00:20:37.988 --> 00:20:41.616
These protests cannot impact our plans
nor our mission to Titan.

310
00:20:41.617 --> 00:20:44.285
And to that end.
I wish to discuss where we stand

311
00:20:44.286 --> 00:20:46.871
on finding those responsible
for the breach.

312
00:20:46.872 --> 00:20:49.832
Our investigators are
already looking at it as we speak.

313
00:20:49.833 --> 00:20:53.253
The same investigators who allowed this
to happen in the first place?

314
00:20:54.213 --> 00:20:58.466
The files came from Helios. so we
would like to question your employees.

315
00:20:58.467 --> 00:20:59.550
Not a chance.

316
00:20:59.551 --> 00:21:00.886
That won't be necessary.

317
00:21:03.222 --> 00:21:04.806
I know who took the files.

318
00:21:34.795 --> 00:21:36.505
[people chattering]

319
00:22:02.489 --> 00:22:03.490
Alex.

320
00:22:04.199 --> 00:22:05.200
Let's talk.

321
00:22:11.623 --> 00:22:12.708
What are they…

322
00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:15.209
what are they gonna do with Ms. Joshi?

323
00:22:15.210 --> 00:22:18.046
Well. her terminal was used
to access confidential files.

324
00:22:21.175 --> 00:22:23.342
Will she… uh. you know…

325
00:22:23.343 --> 00:22:24.552
Mmm. yeah. She'll be okay.

326
00:22:24.553 --> 00:22:26.096
Because it wasn't her.

327
00:22:27.598 --> 00:22:29.183
But you already knew that. didn't you?

328
00:22:34.479 --> 00:22:35.813
Dev. I had no choice.

329
00:22:35.814 --> 00:22:37.064
Really?

330
00:22:37.065 --> 00:22:39.692
Don't… don't do that.
Don't try to make me feel guilty.

331
00:22:39.693 --> 00:22:42.154
- Not after selling us out.
- Selling you out?

332
00:22:44.156 --> 00:22:46.825
I am the reason why
you're not sitting in jail right now.

333
00:22:49.286 --> 00:22:50.453
So tell me.

334
00:22:50.454 --> 00:22:51.955
how long were you planning this?

335
00:22:53.332 --> 00:22:56.000
From the beginning or from the moment
that you asked for this position?

336
00:22:56.001 --> 00:22:57.211
It wasn't like that.

337
00:22:57.961 --> 00:22:58.962
I just…

338
00:23:00.088 --> 00:23:01.589
I was trying to do my job.

339
00:23:01.590 --> 00:23:03.467
And then I saw what Helios was doing.

340
00:23:05.552 --> 00:23:07.220
Dev. I couldn't unsee that.

341
00:23:07.221 --> 00:23:08.387
So it was impulsive.

342
00:23:08.388 --> 00:23:09.472
And selfish.

343
00:23:09.473 --> 00:23:12.266
- That makes me feel so much better.
- I did what I thought was right.

344
00:23:12.267 --> 00:23:14.977
They were the actions of a fucking child.

345
00:23:14.978 --> 00:23:17.730
A child with no awareness
of the consequences.

346
00:23:17.731 --> 00:23:18.732
[scoffs]

347
00:23:21.568 --> 00:23:23.320
You're the one
who's only thinking of himself.

348
00:23:32.371 --> 00:23:36.332
You think I'm doing this for myself?

349
00:23:36.333 --> 00:23:40.462
Dev. you sit up here on a mountain.

350
00:23:41.129 --> 00:23:43.798
Away from everybody.
just playing with people's lives.

351
00:23:43.799 --> 00:23:46.176
But you don't really give
a shit about this place.

352
00:23:47.594 --> 00:23:49.303
About what my grandfather really wanted.

353
00:23:49.304 --> 00:23:54.935
One day you'll understand that everything
that I have done has been for the future.

354
00:23:55.769 --> 00:23:56.770
For your future.

355
00:23:57.938 --> 00:24:02.024
Automation leads to Meru.
Meru leads to a self-sufficient Mars.

356
00:24:02.025 --> 00:24:03.860
That is what your grandfather wanted.

357
00:24:03.861 --> 00:24:05.737
Do you really think that he wanted this?

358
00:24:06.363 --> 00:24:09.283
A Mars that only a chosen few
get to be a part of? Really?

359
00:24:10.492 --> 00:24:11.660
Really?

360
00:24:13.954 --> 00:24:15.914
You have no idea
what my grandfather wanted.

361
00:24:24.673 --> 00:24:25.674
What are you doing?

362
00:24:27.342 --> 00:24:28.343
I quit.

363
00:24:33.891 --> 00:24:34.892
[sighs]

364
00:24:41.315 --> 00:24:42.399
[sighs]

365
00:24:44.902 --> 00:24:46.778
[protesters clamoring]

366
00:25:03.378 --> 00:25:05.005
[no audible dialogue]

367
00:25:10.511 --> 00:25:12.054
[no audible dialogue]

368
00:25:38.830 --> 00:25:40.332
[sighs]

369
00:25:46.296 --> 00:25:47.381
Mandy?

370
00:26:27.713 --> 00:26:29.173
[typing]

371
00:26:32.718 --> 00:26:33.969
[computer beeps]

372
00:26:38.765 --> 00:26:39.891
[typing]

373
00:26:39.892 --> 00:26:41.475
What are you doing?

374
00:26:41.476 --> 00:26:44.062
- Hey. Lily. I was just. uh...
- You were looking through my shit.

375
00:26:44.646 --> 00:26:46.439
Don't talk to me with that tone.

376
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:47.982
My tone? What are you talking about?

377
00:26:47.983 --> 00:26:50.484
- You're going through my stuff.
- You're damn right I am.

378
00:26:50.485 --> 00:26:52.946
I'm gonna be straight with you. Lily.
You're in trouble.

379
00:26:53.864 --> 00:26:55.407
What are you talking about?

380
00:26:56.074 --> 00:26:57.492
They know you're behind this leak.

381
00:26:58.493 --> 00:26:59.494
This is serious.

382
00:27:00.245 --> 00:27:02.997
Yeah. I don't give a shit
if Tulane revokes my...

383
00:27:02.998 --> 00:27:06.167
This isn't about college anymore!
They're talking about prison time!

384
00:27:06.168 --> 00:27:08.295
These people don't fuck around.
believe me.

385
00:27:12.883 --> 00:27:13.884
Look…

386
00:27:16.845 --> 00:27:18.429
they know you're the one who let it out.

387
00:27:18.430 --> 00:27:22.308
They just want to know who took
the information in the first place.

388
00:27:22.309 --> 00:27:23.602
Not a fucking chance.

389
00:27:24.186 --> 00:27:25.603
Lily. be reasonable here.

390
00:27:25.604 --> 00:27:27.855
You're asking me to rat someone out. to…

391
00:27:27.856 --> 00:27:29.440
what? To protect myself?

392
00:27:29.441 --> 00:27:30.525
No. What I'm ask…

393
00:27:30.526 --> 00:27:33.194
what I'm asking you to do
is not destroy your entire life.

394
00:27:33.195 --> 00:27:35.613
They are the ones who are
destroying my entire life.

395
00:27:35.614 --> 00:27:36.864
Lily...

396
00:27:36.865 --> 00:27:38.533
I can't believe
you would ask me to do that.

397
00:27:38.534 --> 00:27:39.868
I'm just trying to protect you. kiddo.

398
00:27:43.038 --> 00:27:44.164
This isn't about me.

399
00:27:44.831 --> 00:27:45.958
It's about all of us.

400
00:27:49.920 --> 00:27:51.004
Lily.

401
00:27:52.130 --> 00:27:53.715
Come back here. Lily!

402
00:27:56.927 --> 00:27:57.928
[door closes]

403
00:28:04.059 --> 00:28:05.143
[sighs]

404
00:28:15.237 --> 00:28:17.029
Dispatch. Thirty-seven.

405
00:28:17.030 --> 00:28:18.739
I got another 10-17B.

406
00:28:18.740 --> 00:28:20.116
[dispatch] <i>Copy that. 37.</i>

407
00:28:20.117 --> 00:28:23.077
<i>Collect photographic evidence
and submit by end of shift.</i>

408
00:28:23.078 --> 00:28:24.245
[shutter clicks]

409
00:28:24.246 --> 00:28:25.997
[people chattering]

410
00:28:25.998 --> 00:28:27.249
[typing]

411
00:28:29.126 --> 00:28:31.336
[chattering continues]

412
00:28:39.094 --> 00:28:40.803
- [computer chimes]
- All right.

413
00:28:40.804 --> 00:28:42.806
Your suit will come out to you in a few.

414
00:28:43.515 --> 00:28:45.893
Please be more careful
with the HUT this time.

415
00:28:52.191 --> 00:28:54.317
Officer Boyd. Need a suit?

416
00:28:54.318 --> 00:28:55.652
No. I. uh…

417
00:28:56.278 --> 00:28:58.112
You know. it's the stupidest thing.

418
00:28:58.113 --> 00:29:01.450
My paycheck didn't have hazard pay for
the last few times I was on surface duty.

419
00:29:02.075 --> 00:29:05.828
Dispatch is giving me shit.
so I need to cross-check the dates.

420
00:29:05.829 --> 00:29:08.164
- You mind if I…
- Sorry. no can do.

421
00:29:08.165 --> 00:29:10.333
Not without an official request
from base HR.

422
00:29:10.334 --> 00:29:11.709
[groans]

423
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:13.544
You'd be doing me a solid. Shaw.

424
00:29:13.545 --> 00:29:16.380
I-I really need that hazard pay
to make my monthly nut.

425
00:29:16.381 --> 00:29:17.673
I hear you on that.

426
00:29:17.674 --> 00:29:20.801
All these protests? Kids could learn
a thing or two about monthly nuts.

427
00:29:20.802 --> 00:29:21.969
Right? [laughs]

428
00:29:21.970 --> 00:29:24.055
Nothing better to do
than stand in everybody's way.

429
00:29:24.056 --> 00:29:25.140
Yeah.

430
00:29:32.981 --> 00:29:34.483
[typing]

431
00:29:35.609 --> 00:29:37.903
All right. Just make it quick.

432
00:29:38.529 --> 00:29:39.821
Thank you.

433
00:29:41.698 --> 00:29:43.951
- [mouse clicks]
- [typing]

434
00:29:50.958 --> 00:29:52.709
[mouse wheel scrolling]

435
00:30:16.692 --> 00:30:17.943
[shutter clicks]

436
00:30:20.654 --> 00:30:21.864
[shutter clicking]

437
00:30:23.031 --> 00:30:24.116
[shutter clicks]

438
00:30:41.758 --> 00:30:44.594
<i>The asteroid belt's not like it is
in the movies.</i>

439
00:30:44.595 --> 00:30:48.514
<i>They're much further apart.
so no need for any fancy piloting.</i>

440
00:30:48.515 --> 00:30:49.850
[Alex] Mm-hmm.

441
00:30:51.435 --> 00:30:54.312
<i>But then we were chased
by some TIE fighters</i>

442
00:30:54.313 --> 00:30:56.480
<i>and had to land on an asteroid.</i>

443
00:30:56.481 --> 00:30:59.066
<i>Yeah. we were in
a big damp cave full of mynocks.</i>

444
00:30:59.067 --> 00:31:03.697
<i>and it turns out the cave was
a giant creature that nearly ate us.</i>

445
00:31:04.823 --> 00:31:06.240
- What?
- [sighs]

446
00:31:06.241 --> 00:31:07.658
<i>And he's back.</i>

447
00:31:07.659 --> 00:31:08.827
Uh…

448
00:31:09.953 --> 00:31:11.329
Sorry. Sorry.

449
00:31:11.330 --> 00:31:12.413
<i>That's okay.</i>

450
00:31:12.414 --> 00:31:16.167
<i>I'm just trying to take advantage
of us being able to talk in real time</i>

451
00:31:16.168 --> 00:31:17.752
<i>before the delay gets too bad.</i>

452
00:31:17.753 --> 00:31:18.754
[Alex] I know.

453
00:31:19.338 --> 00:31:20.464
I know. I just…

454
00:31:21.840 --> 00:31:23.050
Um…

455
00:31:25.928 --> 00:31:27.054
<i>Are you okay?</i>

456
00:31:27.888 --> 00:31:29.139
<i>What's going on?</i>

457
00:31:31.266 --> 00:31:32.643
I quit Helios.

458
00:31:33.685 --> 00:31:35.479
<i>Because of what was in the data breach?</i>

459
00:31:37.856 --> 00:31:39.107
Yeah.

460
00:31:39.733 --> 00:31:41.275
[sighs] <i>I'm sorry. sweetheart.</i>

461
00:31:41.276 --> 00:31:42.653
<i>That couldn't have been easy.</i>

462
00:31:43.862 --> 00:31:45.030
No. I…

463
00:31:47.115 --> 00:31:49.409
I just feel like I'm finally
doing something meaningful.

464
00:31:50.786 --> 00:31:53.872
You know? Like. I-I finally get what
Poppy was saying all that time.

465
00:31:55.374 --> 00:31:56.875
It just sucks I wasn't listening.

466
00:31:57.501 --> 00:32:02.255
<i>Well. I'm so glad to hear that
you're feeling inspired by all of this.</i>

467
00:32:02.256 --> 00:32:09.179
<i>but things like this. they can take
a turn and get really dangerous fast.</i>

468
00:32:10.013 --> 00:32:13.391
<i>Look. I don't know how much you remember
of what happened in '03.</i>

469
00:32:13.392 --> 00:32:15.059
<i>but things got really scary.</i>

470
00:32:15.060 --> 00:32:16.978
<i>and I didn't even know
if I could take care of you.</i>

471
00:32:16.979 --> 00:32:19.021
[stammers] This is. uh. different. Mom.

472
00:32:19.022 --> 00:32:20.106
<i>I know.</i>

473
00:32:20.107 --> 00:32:23.610
<i>Just promise me you'll be careful.</i>

474
00:32:24.194 --> 00:32:26.612
- Yeah. Of course.
- <i>Okay.</i>

475
00:32:26.613 --> 00:32:28.073
<i>Well. I gotta go.</i>

476
00:32:28.866 --> 00:32:31.033
[sighs] <i>I miss you. sweetheart.</i>

477
00:32:31.034 --> 00:32:32.077
I miss you too.

478
00:32:33.078 --> 00:32:34.787
And. uh. you stay out of Cloud City. yeah?

479
00:32:34.788 --> 00:32:36.790
- [chuckles]
- I heard Lando's up to something.

480
00:32:37.332 --> 00:32:38.625
<i>You were listening.</i>

481
00:32:39.334 --> 00:32:40.335
<i>I love you.</i>

482
00:32:40.961 --> 00:32:43.172
- <i>Always.</i>
- [chuckles] Yeah. I love you.

483
00:32:44.798 --> 00:32:45.924
[computer beeps]

484
00:32:59.646 --> 00:33:00.813
[Walt] <i>Systems nominal.</i>

485
00:33:00.814 --> 00:33:02.982
<i>except for a slight drop
in the accumulator pressure</i>

486
00:33:02.983 --> 00:33:05.109
<i>in the number four TCS loop.</i>

487
00:33:05.110 --> 00:33:07.695
<i>It'd be great if you can take a look
at the telemetry.</i>

488
00:33:07.696 --> 00:33:10.239
<i>Uh. apart from that. things are fine.</i>

489
00:33:10.240 --> 00:33:12.242
<i>Not nearly the drama you've been having.</i>

490
00:33:13.619 --> 00:33:15.745
How's tokamak containment trending?

491
00:33:15.746 --> 00:33:17.663
<i>Field stability still looking good.</i>

492
00:33:17.664 --> 00:33:19.624
<i>Superconductor performance nominal.</i>

493
00:33:19.625 --> 00:33:23.002
We'll uplink the harmonics analysis
as soon as we get it from Helios. Houston.

494
00:33:23.003 --> 00:33:24.338
<i>Okay. copy that.</i>

495
00:33:24.838 --> 00:33:25.881
How's crew morale?

496
00:33:26.465 --> 00:33:27.591
<i>Good. You know.</i>

497
00:33:28.342 --> 00:33:30.218
<i>Everyone's doing their job.</i>

498
00:33:30.219 --> 00:33:32.136
<i>It's a long road ahead though.</i>

499
00:33:32.137 --> 00:33:34.388
<i>We still have our challenges.</i>

500
00:33:34.389 --> 00:33:35.766
Yeah. I hear that.

501
00:33:43.148 --> 00:33:44.441
Um…

502
00:33:45.150 --> 00:33:47.903
let us know if you see anything weird
in the field symmetry.

503
00:33:48.403 --> 00:33:50.197
- <i>All right. Signing off.</i>
- Thanks.

504
00:33:55.118 --> 00:33:56.202
Can I help you?

505
00:33:56.203 --> 00:33:57.746
[Irina] It is incredible.

506
00:33:58.789 --> 00:34:00.457
They're still so close to us.

507
00:34:01.041 --> 00:34:03.000
But such a long way to go.

508
00:34:03.001 --> 00:34:05.127
Yeah. well. it's not really
viewing hours. So…

509
00:34:05.128 --> 00:34:08.632
This is all very impressive.
your new home.

510
00:34:09.550 --> 00:34:11.384
How long will you stay?

511
00:34:11.385 --> 00:34:13.636
Until they land at least. And you?

512
00:34:13.637 --> 00:34:14.847
When do you leave?

513
00:34:15.973 --> 00:34:18.976
[chuckles] To be determined.

514
00:34:19.518 --> 00:34:23.688
Kuragin has many concerns
at Happy Valley to be seen to.

515
00:34:27.317 --> 00:34:30.362
I still don't understand how
you underbid us for the space elevator.

516
00:34:31.612 --> 00:34:33.573
I'm sure you and the Governor
being from the same country

517
00:34:33.574 --> 00:34:35.783
had nothing to do with it.

518
00:34:35.784 --> 00:34:40.038
Well. that is the nature
of capitalism. is it not?

519
00:34:40.873 --> 00:34:42.623
You must always be growing.

520
00:34:44.208 --> 00:34:47.254
Stealing information from a competitor
isn't really capitalism.

521
00:34:48.213 --> 00:34:49.339
It's just stealing.

522
00:34:49.922 --> 00:34:52.759
Now if you'll excuse me.
I need to get back to Helios.

523
00:34:53.260 --> 00:34:54.594
[Irina] How is she?

524
00:35:00.392 --> 00:35:02.436
You mean how is she doing in prison?

525
00:35:07.566 --> 00:35:08.649
Yeah.

526
00:35:08.650 --> 00:35:09.943
She's just peachy.

527
00:35:21.955 --> 00:35:23.665
- [in Russian] Goodbye. little rabbit.
- Hmm.

528
00:35:27.628 --> 00:35:28.754
[kisses]

529
00:35:29.630 --> 00:35:31.256
I will miss you.

530
00:35:33.133 --> 00:35:34.759
Someone has been drinking.

531
00:35:34.760 --> 00:35:37.137
- [groans] Come on.
- [chuckles]

532
00:35:41.934 --> 00:35:42.976
You know…

533
00:35:44.102 --> 00:35:46.313
protests are starting on <i>Phoenix</i> now.

534
00:35:47.814 --> 00:35:51.985
They've even found 'Free Mars' graffiti
on the asteroid.

535
00:35:53.487 --> 00:35:56.406
If you can believe it. the asteroid.

536
00:35:58.450 --> 00:35:59.743
[sighs]

537
00:36:00.786 --> 00:36:02.204
We will get through this.

538
00:36:02.704 --> 00:36:03.955
- Hmm?
- [grunts]

539
00:36:03.956 --> 00:36:04.957
Be strong.

540
00:36:16.802 --> 00:36:17.970
[moans]

541
00:36:20.639 --> 00:36:21.682
Kiss Mishka for me.

542
00:36:24.685 --> 00:36:25.893
Love you.

543
00:36:25.894 --> 00:36:27.145
[both] Mmm.

544
00:36:42.870 --> 00:36:43.871
[sighs]

545
00:37:05.309 --> 00:37:06.727
[protesters clamoring]

546
00:37:12.941 --> 00:37:14.401
[clamoring continues]

547
00:37:16.570 --> 00:37:17.613
[in English] Hello.

548
00:37:18.739 --> 00:37:19.907
Hi. everybody.

549
00:37:21.074 --> 00:37:22.909
[clamoring stops]

550
00:37:22.910 --> 00:37:24.952
Hello. sir. Where are you from?

551
00:37:24.953 --> 00:37:26.078
- Nigeria.
- Nigeria.

552
00:37:26.079 --> 00:37:28.123
Very good football team.
Soccer. [chuckles]

553
00:37:29.333 --> 00:37:30.959
Hi. How are you?

554
00:37:32.878 --> 00:37:34.212
Where are you from?

555
00:37:34.213 --> 00:37:36.131
I'm from Mars. asshole.

556
00:37:37.174 --> 00:37:38.424
I'm from Mars too.

557
00:37:38.425 --> 00:37:40.384
- [protesters shouting. clamoring]
- I'm from Mars too!

558
00:37:40.385 --> 00:37:42.303
[protester 1] I'm from Mars. you asshole!

559
00:37:42.304 --> 00:37:44.472
- [protester 2] Now get out of here!
- [protester 3] I'm from Mars.

560
00:37:44.473 --> 00:37:46.350
[protesters jeering]

561
00:37:51.647 --> 00:37:53.273
Hey. Alex. Hey. How are you?

562
00:37:54.900 --> 00:37:55.984
It is good to see you.

563
00:37:57.027 --> 00:37:58.237
I could use your help.

564
00:37:58.987 --> 00:38:00.447
You shouldn't be here.

565
00:38:01.240 --> 00:38:02.323
I'm not the enemy.

566
00:38:02.324 --> 00:38:03.867
[Alex] You represent the M-6.

567
00:38:05.327 --> 00:38:07.578
You're trying to take away people's jobs.
their homes.

568
00:38:07.579 --> 00:38:09.414
[Lily] Yeah. I mean. we grew up here.

569
00:38:09.998 --> 00:38:11.415
This place means everything to us.

570
00:38:11.416 --> 00:38:14.377
And you treat it
as if it's somewhere we want to leave.

571
00:38:14.378 --> 00:38:15.754
[Lily] Mars is ours.

572
00:38:16.421 --> 00:38:18.130
- Mars is ours!
- Mars is ours!

573
00:38:18.131 --> 00:38:20.091
[protesters chanting] Mars is ours!

574
00:38:20.092 --> 00:38:24.971
Mars is ours!

575
00:38:24.972 --> 00:38:26.932
[chanting continues]

576
00:38:28.559 --> 00:38:30.518
- Listen! Mars is ours!
- Mars is ours!

577
00:38:30.519 --> 00:38:32.103
Mars is ours!

578
00:38:32.104 --> 00:38:33.814
[chanting continues]

579
00:38:35.732 --> 00:38:39.111
Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

580
00:38:40.779 --> 00:38:42.613
- Is the shipment on time?
- It is. sir.

581
00:38:42.614 --> 00:38:44.157
Arrival at 1100 tomorrow.

582
00:38:44.992 --> 00:38:47.952
- Governor.
- Where is. uh. Comrade Bolkonski?

583
00:38:47.953 --> 00:38:50.621
On <i>Phoenix.</i>
He has arranged quarters there.

584
00:38:50.622 --> 00:38:52.624
The gravity here does not agree with him.

585
00:38:53.792 --> 00:38:54.918
[in Russian] What is wrong?

586
00:38:56.962 --> 00:38:59.882
I thought perhaps these protesters
could be reasoned with. but…

587
00:39:00.215 --> 00:39:02.259
- they will not listen.
- [sighs]

588
00:39:03.010 --> 00:39:05.053
You have allowed things to escalate.

589
00:39:05.470 --> 00:39:10.142
Now the only way to put out this fire
is starve it of oxygen.

590
00:39:22.696 --> 00:39:26.200
[in English] I am declaring
a base-wide curfew per Mars Charter.

591
00:39:27.075 --> 00:39:28.534
Have your officers clear the area.

592
00:39:28.535 --> 00:39:30.871
Arrest everybody who doesn't comply.

593
00:39:31.747 --> 00:39:33.624
There will be no more demonstrations.

594
00:39:34.791 --> 00:39:36.877
Yes. sir. We've trained for it.

595
00:39:37.711 --> 00:39:39.004
I'll take care of it.

596
00:39:40.339 --> 00:39:42.382
[in Russian]
Let's hope you've made a wise decision.

597
00:39:42.925 --> 00:39:44.301
For both of our sakes.

598
00:39:49.515 --> 00:39:52.976
[dispatch. in English] <i>Peacekeepers
report to central security station.</i>

599
00:39:58.690 --> 00:39:59.691
Hey.

600
00:40:08.116 --> 00:40:09.409
What's going on. partner?

601
00:40:13.705 --> 00:40:15.081
[Celia] You were out there that night.

602
00:40:15.082 --> 00:40:16.458
You lied to me.

603
00:40:19.378 --> 00:40:20.921
What. you got nothing to say?

604
00:40:22.631 --> 00:40:23.714
[chuckles]

605
00:40:23.715 --> 00:40:25.299
Okay. I'll ask Madoun.

606
00:40:25.300 --> 00:40:27.760
- He was out there too. I got his ID...
- No. no. Just hold on.

607
00:40:27.761 --> 00:40:30.055
Just hold on.
Just fucking hold on for a second. okay?

608
00:40:30.764 --> 00:40:32.558
- You don't understand.
- Yeah. of course I do.

609
00:40:33.267 --> 00:40:34.768
You've been lying to my face for weeks.

610
00:40:35.769 --> 00:40:38.062
You were there. you knew
that Yoon worked those shipments.

611
00:40:38.063 --> 00:40:39.898
and you didn't say anything
after he was killed.

612
00:40:40.774 --> 00:40:42.024
I've been trying to help you.

613
00:40:42.025 --> 00:40:43.193
[softly] Come on.

614
00:40:45.571 --> 00:40:48.114
Look. I understand Madoun
holding out on me.

615
00:40:48.115 --> 00:40:49.615
'cause he's a piece of shit.

616
00:40:49.616 --> 00:40:52.786
- But you're supposed to be my partner.
- I am your partner. goddamn it.

617
00:40:53.537 --> 00:40:56.623
I have been trying to help you.
but you just don't see it.

618
00:40:57.332 --> 00:40:58.958
You won't listen. I…

619
00:40:58.959 --> 00:41:00.877
You think you know everything.
You think you know best.

620
00:41:00.878 --> 00:41:03.671
You think you have some secret line
to the Almighty himself. But you don't.

621
00:41:03.672 --> 00:41:05.464
You just make shit worse
for everybody here.

622
00:41:05.465 --> 00:41:06.800
Yourself. especially.

623
00:41:07.885 --> 00:41:09.969
[stammers] What are you doing?
You're sticking your nose in everywhere.

624
00:41:09.970 --> 00:41:11.471
[stammers] You're talking to Craters.

625
00:41:12.055 --> 00:41:13.848
You're making waves at Kuragin.

626
00:41:13.849 --> 00:41:15.142
Like. just stop.

627
00:41:18.812 --> 00:41:24.985
I never… I never told you…
I was talking to a Crater.

628
00:41:30.115 --> 00:41:32.201
I never told anyone why I was down there.

629
00:41:32.784 --> 00:41:34.703
No. you told me. You did. remember?

630
00:41:36.872 --> 00:41:38.290
No. we talked about that.

631
00:41:40.167 --> 00:41:42.127
No. The only way you would know that…

632
00:41:43.754 --> 00:41:45.130
is if you were the one…

633
00:41:51.929 --> 00:41:53.222
That was you down there…

634
00:41:55.599 --> 00:41:56.642
following me.

635
00:41:57.518 --> 00:41:58.560
Uh…

636
00:42:02.523 --> 00:42:03.856
I was trying to protect you.

637
00:42:03.857 --> 00:42:05.733
By hitting me in the head
with a fucking pipe?

638
00:42:05.734 --> 00:42:07.402
No. I… [sighs]

639
00:42:09.279 --> 00:42:11.114
- [sighs]
- Fred. are you a part of this?

640
00:42:14.493 --> 00:42:15.577
[grunts]

641
00:42:16.828 --> 00:42:17.955
Did you…

642
00:42:25.254 --> 00:42:26.755
I didn't mean to.

643
00:42:28.715 --> 00:42:30.383
- Oh. fuck.
- I didn't.

644
00:42:30.384 --> 00:42:32.052
Shit just got out of control.

645
00:42:33.637 --> 00:42:35.304
Yoon… Yoon was making all these threats.

646
00:42:35.305 --> 00:42:37.974
He was threatening to go public about
the automation if they didn't pay him off.

647
00:42:37.975 --> 00:42:39.852
- So you killed him?
- I… I…

648
00:42:42.229 --> 00:42:43.980
[stammers] It was an accident.

649
00:42:43.981 --> 00:42:45.773
- Oh. fuck.
- No. you gotta believe me. C.

650
00:42:45.774 --> 00:42:47.483
It was an accident.
It was an accident. H-He…

651
00:42:47.484 --> 00:42:49.652
You know. they told me and Vince
to take him out in a rover

652
00:42:49.653 --> 00:42:51.612
- and scare him a little bit.
- Jesus fucking Christ.

653
00:42:51.613 --> 00:42:54.448
And then he just… he refused.
He wouldn't stop going nuts.

654
00:42:54.449 --> 00:42:57.369
- He came after me. C. and then...
- We're supposed to protect these people.

655
00:42:59.037 --> 00:43:00.038
[sighs]

656
00:43:00.539 --> 00:43:01.582
Man…

657
00:43:03.208 --> 00:43:04.751
I told you to leave it alone.

658
00:43:06.879 --> 00:43:08.172
I told you.

659
00:43:11.133 --> 00:43:12.509
How could you do this?

660
00:43:16.680 --> 00:43:17.890
I don't know.

661
00:43:20.893 --> 00:43:22.477
I don't know. I fucked up.

662
00:43:23.812 --> 00:43:25.772
I fucked… I fucked up.

663
00:43:26.481 --> 00:43:28.608
And. uh. I never meant
for it to go this far.

664
00:43:28.609 --> 00:43:30.234
I just wanted it all to go away.

665
00:43:30.235 --> 00:43:31.361
Wrong answer.

666
00:43:35.282 --> 00:43:36.617
I may have to tell Palmer.

667
00:43:37.534 --> 00:43:39.203
- I'm sorry. Fred. but I'm gonna have to.
- C… C…

668
00:43:40.662 --> 00:43:43.040
who do you think told me
to go handle Yoon in the first place?

669
00:43:45.417 --> 00:43:47.126
[Palmer] All right. people. Listen up!

670
00:43:47.127 --> 00:43:48.295
[indistinct chattering]

671
00:43:58.847 --> 00:44:00.682
[Palmer] You've all trained for this.

672
00:44:02.684 --> 00:44:05.646
We will enforce this curfew
with no exceptions.

673
00:44:06.605 --> 00:44:09.482
I want this clean. I want this efficient.

674
00:44:09.483 --> 00:44:11.609
I want this by the book. understand?

675
00:44:11.610 --> 00:44:13.152
[peacekeepers] Yes. sir!

676
00:44:13.153 --> 00:44:16.365
[Palmer] I want protocol
to be followed to a tee. people.

677
00:44:17.324 --> 00:44:21.327
Any noncompliance or resisting an officer
will result in arrest.

678
00:44:21.328 --> 00:44:23.163
- Clear?
- [peacekeepers] Yes. sir!

679
00:44:24.289 --> 00:44:25.541
All right.

680
00:44:26.124 --> 00:44:27.209
Line it up!

681
00:44:32.923 --> 00:44:34.299
[exhales sharply]

682
00:44:39.888 --> 00:44:41.265
[sighs] Move it out.

683
00:44:44.268 --> 00:44:46.602
- You know this is bullshit. man. Guys.
- If the cops are gone. slow down.

684
00:44:46.603 --> 00:44:49.313
- The cops? Fuck the cops. man.
- Slow down.

685
00:44:49.314 --> 00:44:51.232
They're stepping all over us.
You know that.

686
00:44:51.233 --> 00:44:52.776
- If we don't do something… What?
- Ger. Ger.

687
00:44:53.902 --> 00:44:55.736
You need to calm down.

688
00:44:55.737 --> 00:44:57.655
These protests aren't doing shit.

689
00:44:57.656 --> 00:44:58.657
We gotta do more.

690
00:44:59.908 --> 00:45:01.534
Okay. Like what?

691
00:45:01.535 --> 00:45:04.537
I don't know. Go to MOCC.
the governor's office. something.

692
00:45:04.538 --> 00:45:07.456
- We gotta make them listen.
- They're just looking for an excuse

693
00:45:07.457 --> 00:45:09.500
to come back here and arrest us.

694
00:45:09.501 --> 00:45:11.210
- Don't give 'em one.
- Come on. That's bullshit.

695
00:45:11.211 --> 00:45:12.753
You know that's bullshit.

696
00:45:12.754 --> 00:45:14.047
Give me this.

697
00:45:15.257 --> 00:45:17.800
Mars is ours!

698
00:45:17.801 --> 00:45:19.886
[protesters cheering. chanting]
Mars is ours!

699
00:45:19.887 --> 00:45:23.055
Mars is ours!

700
00:45:23.056 --> 00:45:24.850
[chanting continues]

701
00:45:30.856 --> 00:45:33.900
[voice on PA] <i>Please remain
in your HAB until further notice.</i>

702
00:45:33.901 --> 00:45:35.944
[voice 2 on PA. repeating in Russian]

703
00:45:39.656 --> 00:45:42.492
Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

704
00:45:47.372 --> 00:45:48.415
[chanting stops]

705
00:45:49.833 --> 00:45:52.252
[protesters clamoring. jeering]

706
00:45:53.545 --> 00:45:56.673
Attention. Disperse immediately.

707
00:45:57.716 --> 00:46:01.887
You are in violation of curfew
and this is an unlawful assembly.

708
00:46:02.930 --> 00:46:04.931
Disperse immediately.

709
00:46:04.932 --> 00:46:07.893
- Fuck you!
- This is a peaceful protest!

710
00:46:10.771 --> 00:46:14.815
Disperse now or you will be dispersed.

711
00:46:14.816 --> 00:46:17.653
[protesters clamoring. jeering]

712
00:46:27.371 --> 00:46:29.164
Mars is ours!

713
00:46:30.290 --> 00:46:33.417
[protesters] Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

714
00:46:33.418 --> 00:46:35.837
Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

715
00:46:35.838 --> 00:46:37.548
This is your final warning.

716
00:46:38.131 --> 00:46:39.842
- Disperse now.
- [chanting continues]

717
00:46:50.769 --> 00:46:53.646
Peacekeepers! Clear the street.

718
00:46:53.647 --> 00:46:56.066
[chanting continues]

719
00:47:01.196 --> 00:47:02.406
We're not scared of you.

720
00:47:03.991 --> 00:47:05.074
Forward!

721
00:47:05.075 --> 00:47:08.203
[clamoring]

722
00:47:14.293 --> 00:47:17.253
[voice 1 on PA] <i>Please remain
in your HAB until further notice.</i>

723
00:47:17.254 --> 00:47:21.300
[voice 2 on PA. repeating in Russian]

724
00:47:21.842 --> 00:47:24.468
[voice 1] <i>Please remain
in your HAB until further notice.</i>

725
00:47:24.469 --> 00:47:27.430
[voice 2 repeating in Russian]

726
00:47:27.431 --> 00:47:30.766
[protesters] Mars is ours!
Mars is ours! Mars is ours!

727
00:47:30.767 --> 00:47:32.561
[chanting continues]

728
00:47:33.312 --> 00:47:34.980
[clamoring. shouting]

729
00:47:39.151 --> 00:47:41.485
You! Do not move! Stand down!

730
00:47:41.486 --> 00:47:42.487
Fuck you!

731
00:47:44.781 --> 00:47:46.617
[grunting. screaming]

732
00:47:47.701 --> 00:47:49.619
Hey. man. get off me!

733
00:47:49.620 --> 00:47:51.037
Don't fucking touch me!

734
00:47:51.038 --> 00:47:52.831
- Don't fucking touch me!
- [protester screams]

735
00:47:59.379 --> 00:48:00.464
Hey!

736
00:48:01.340 --> 00:48:03.342
- [screaming]
- Get off me! Fuck you!

737
00:48:03.926 --> 00:48:05.343
Get off me!

738
00:48:05.344 --> 00:48:07.304
- [screaming]
- [Celia] Back up!

739
00:48:13.393 --> 00:48:17.272
- [screams] Let her go! Lily! Lily!
- Mom! Mom!

740
00:48:19.191 --> 00:48:20.526
[Mandy grunts] Lily!

741
00:48:21.193 --> 00:48:23.069
- Lily!
- Mom!

742
00:48:23.070 --> 00:48:24.613
Get off! [grunts]

743
00:48:29.826 --> 00:48:32.496
- [grunts] I said stand down now!
- [grunting]

744
00:48:33.664 --> 00:48:35.374
[grunts] Ow! [screams]

745
00:48:46.677 --> 00:48:48.053
Lily!

746
00:48:59.314 --> 00:49:00.649
[grunts]

747
00:49:01.859 --> 00:49:03.360
[grunting]

748
00:49:08.782 --> 00:49:10.658
[grunts. screams]

749
00:49:10.659 --> 00:49:11.827
[grunts]

750
00:49:14.830 --> 00:49:15.831
Lily.

751
00:49:17.249 --> 00:49:18.583
Lily!

752
00:49:18.584 --> 00:49:19.626
Lily. baby. wake up.

753
00:49:20.294 --> 00:49:21.670
[groaning]

754
00:49:25.007 --> 00:49:27.301
- [explosions]
- [protesters screaming]

755
00:49:29.136 --> 00:49:31.722
[grunting]

756
00:49:33.765 --> 00:49:35.267
[straining]

757
00:49:36.351 --> 00:49:37.518
[screams]

758
00:49:37.519 --> 00:49:40.104
No! No! No. not like this!

759
00:49:40.105 --> 00:49:42.858
Protect yourselves!

760
00:49:45.152 --> 00:49:46.528
[protesters screaming]

761
00:49:51.200 --> 00:49:52.701
[grunts]

762
00:49:57.080 --> 00:49:58.081
Retreat!

763
00:50:01.460 --> 00:50:04.253
Come on! Come on! Follow me!

764
00:50:04.254 --> 00:50:05.422
Come on!

765
00:50:06.757 --> 00:50:09.009
[alarm blaring]

766
